[
  {
    "id": "PRO.4.1",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Hear, ye children, the instruction of a father, and attend to know understanding.",
    "hash": "47f3a1a57566d22f2f2d41d6b910c9f7c2c4573236c12641567eb587cac24ea0"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.4.2",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "For I give you good doctrine, forsake ye not my law.",
    "hash": "1c3141c68e56755d71b7b128329b274784b3d6053b0f10907cd8431cae3a4130"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.4.3",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "For I was my father's son, tender and only {beloved} in the sight of my mother.",
    "hash": "ae1431ded8fe9af94d16d22078096e804973dc3c149d60418d0b18bf935fea7f"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.4.4",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "He taught me also, and said unto me, Let thine heart retain my words: keep my commandments, and live.",
    "hash": "77ace332006469936e5a13fd6643130fcc17c12ed91d3419b2e8cac9ea226129"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.4.5",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "Get wisdom, get understanding: forget {it} not; neither decline from the words of my mouth.",
    "hash": "a037cc83f9c49d9cf3ccd2aae119b767a0d6a511e1ce7901d024941a1257d2d3"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.4.6",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "Forsake her not, and she shall preserve thee: love her, and she shall keep thee.",
    "hash": "c5af70d6a75bd75203a9318a03a2f27c7bf0e629c9626aaa7a7c9617ed62dd32"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.4.7",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "Wisdom {is} the principal thing; {therefore} get wisdom: and with all thy getting get understanding.",
    "hash": "84458650d338db48167f9b16c708d341c0d5100d2db416170a82041f13a1cc0d"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.4.8",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "Exalt her, and she shall promote thee: she shall bring thee to honour, when thou dost embrace her.",
    "hash": "50df53f2be9b16d5542ad049c1d26d28eef0d4671ecca1e3a6b9b2825441d2b7"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.4.9",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "She shall give to thine head an ornament of grace: a crown of glory shall she deliver to thee. {a crown...: or, she shall compass thee with a crown of glory}",
    "hash": "941685b57632dd025b3a9e7cd8a6f730aee3e47d9955d2dc96c8bd25482f17fc"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.4.10",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "Hear, O my son, and receive my sayings; and the years of thy life shall be many.",
    "hash": "91f5092336d0c7cee2d76a41d6170f4255d73b7f95fff34352151bde93b0eaac"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.4.11",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "I have taught thee in the way of wisdom; I have led thee in right paths.",
    "hash": "6d705f33669d696c7a4d547b22c32690740fc4b1d6af14cf848f8a5771632a8e"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.4.12",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "When thou goest, thy steps shall not be straitened; and when thou runnest, thou shalt not stumble.",
    "hash": "77c6bd43fc37eb92b957d689a813a661ebe7793fc618e2373f953bf2cb125098"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.4.13",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "Take fast hold of instruction; let {her} not go: keep her; for she {is} thy life.",
    "hash": "0b17aa020cd13bd73c873702a4cf9c3d6032b11808b11f5779cf794e7756c629"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.4.14",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "Enter not into the path of the wicked, and go not in the way of evil {men}.",
    "hash": "f215d87f2729185ea1ff20d4fdbe00d788325fb97fe66387a563d4d482437654"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.4.15",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "Avoid it, pass not by it, turn from it, and pass away.",
    "hash": "6fa3b69e45eeb216e9671ba4cf16abef9afc807ebbb1a9435ca8482b3c6eb53d"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.4.16",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "For they sleep not, except they have done mischief; and their sleep is taken away, unless they cause {some} to fall.",
    "hash": "be8dcdb4cb95785361fdd935e943346260cb6619969163b4fb6df74a70414554"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.4.17",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "For they eat the bread of wickedness, and drink the wine of violence.",
    "hash": "2414321fa07af6478215f76b78e265b92a535ea4b515923993766c4cc75c2765"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.4.18",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "But the path of the just {is} as the shining light, that shineth more and more unto the perfect day.",
    "hash": "7f3325e0962f7cda20be3e7f483c74f06020da4c5ee96d7cca1a35a4c7d597a1"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.4.19",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "The way of the wicked {is} as darkness: they know not at what they stumble.",
    "hash": "c610b4290632edde47ed59553f2832f26c54b45e363329f60c246ce5a044b8c7"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.4.20",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "My son, attend to my words; incline thine ear unto my sayings.",
    "hash": "1af605803c883114b27293a1e9a9e6d15dd3086562b794017a4a5d96917b0ae2"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.4.21",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "Let them not depart from thine eyes; keep them in the midst of thine heart.",
    "hash": "6d2a678b4eef942e0047099fa497548be20df0c2282e67c23d359387d4ba8c64"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.4.22",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "For they {are} life unto those that find them, and health to all their flesh. {health: Heb. medicine}",
    "hash": "85336cea7e2e01b9f3dff7ba2cc3e8b3dfe4f0096a3269a989454a1e61d5be8f"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.4.23",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "Keep thy heart with all diligence; for out of it {are} the issues of life. {with...: Heb. above all keeping}",
    "hash": "cbf60c7bf3928fca457b9236bfd1233bbaf4f42a9ec0c72ae297ef068d189327"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.4.24",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "Put away from thee a froward mouth, and perverse lips put far from thee. {a froward...: Heb. frowardness of mouth and perverseness of lips}",
    "hash": "a46c52b4b4fff1be8f3f545ef1f2dce45239a9a917dab7fb614718b7ea482bc3"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.4.25",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "Let thine eyes look right on, and let thine eyelids look straight before thee.",
    "hash": "c46c71557cdd383670d92d0777ae57d76fe9bc2030748abd392a1964da5e00ea"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.4.26",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "Ponder the path of thy feet, and let all thy ways be established. {let...: or, all thy ways shall be ordered aright}",
    "hash": "89ce6da29c0a42c9d5bab066e4325d0546b03a643228f38393868e9420f639e9"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.4.27",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 4,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "Turn not to the right hand nor to the left: remove thy foot from evil.",
    "hash": "df845a8e50fe97c45cee0ef2446bc440461fefe3b5d4b22d0040f9d2a2a83811"
  }
]